snippet.textDisplay:
Seriously, this is my favorite song of Super Mario Galaxy. As soon as I went to the level, I thought to myself, "Wow, this is really cool. I like it!". It was an instant hit in my books, and with video game music that doesn't happen very often, for I don't pay attention to music in games until after I go look up the music on Youtube.

But this... This made an impact on my gaming. It made me want to do the best I could on the stage at hand!

snippet.textDisplay: A video game that is an absolute masterpiece is Super Mario Galaxy.  The gameplay utilizes the Wiimote in the best way possible and I feel getting each star involves a quality task.  Super Mario Galaxy shows that the Wii can have excellent graphics if you just put a lot of effort into them.  Koji Kondo continues to amaze people with his music and the orchestra just fits perfectly with a space-themed game.  This game shows that Shigeru Miyamoto can still create excellent games.
